# Environment Root Module Standards

## Required Files

Each `env/<name>/` must contain:
- `versions.tf` — `terraform { required_version, required_providers }`
- `backend.tf` — remote state configuration
- `providers.tf` — provider blocks
- `main.tf` — module composition
- `variables.tf` — all inputs with `type` + `description`
- `outputs.tf` — expose ALB DNS, RDS endpoint, ECS cluster, etc.
- `locals.tf` — common tags and computed values
- `terraform.tfvars.example` — template for required variables

## Version Pinning

```hcl
terraform {
  required_version = "~> 1.5"
  required_providers {
    aws = {
      source  = "hashicorp/aws"
      version = "~> 6.0"
    }
  }
}
```

## Provider Configuration

Keep provider blocks in `providers.tf`, not in `main.tf`.

```hcl
provider "aws" {
  region = var.region
  default_tags {
    tags = local.common_tags
  }
}
```

## Variable Patterns

- Pass `project` and `environment` to every module.
- Sensitive values (`db_password`) must use `sensitive = true` and be supplied via `TF_VAR_*`.
- Never commit `terraform.tfvars` — only commit `terraform.tfvars.example`.

## Outputs

Always output key infrastructure endpoints:

```hcl
output "alb_dns_name" {
  description = "ALB DNS name"
  value       = module.alb.alb_dns_name
}
```
